article.headline: Johnston, Watkins lead UAB over UTSA 33-14
article.description: Tyler Johnston III threw for 294 yards and two touchdowns to help UAB roll to a 33-14 victory over UTSA on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Johnston, Watkins lead UAB over UTSA 33-14

images.name: UAB connects on 67-yard TD
images.caption: Tyler Johnston III lets it fly to Austin Watkins for the 67-yard touchdown to increase UAB's lead on UTSA.

video.headline: UAB connects on 67-yard TD
video.caption: Tyler Johnston III lets it fly to Austin Watkins for the 67-yard touchdown to increase UAB's lead on UTSA.
video.title: UAB connects on 67-yard TD
video.description: Tyler Johnston III lets it fly to Austin Watkins for the 67-yard touchdown to increase UAB's lead on UTSA.

article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Tyler Johnston III threw for 294 yards and two touchdowns to help UAB roll to a 33-14 victory over UTSA on Saturday night. Austin Watkins finished with six catches for 167 yards for UAB (5-1, 2-1 Conference USA). Lucious Stanley had 92 yards rushing on 13 carries. Johnston tossed a 67-yard touchdown pass to Watkins in the second quarter. Myron Mitchell caught his only pass, beating a defender in the end zone for a 25-yard scoring catch that stretched the Blazers lead to 23-14 in the third. Stanley scored on a 5-yard run late in the fourth. Lowell Narcisse was 8 of 19 for 94 yards passing and added 89 yards on the ground to lead UTSA (2-4, 1-2). Sincere McCormick ran for a 4-yard touchdown and Narcisse added a 4-yard scoring run for the Roadrunners.
